WEBVTT

00:02.803 --> 00:05.170
<i>[upbeat saxophone music]</i>

00:05.206 --> 00:07.406
- For this full moon
<i>bruja</i> ceremony,

00:07.441 --> 00:09.541
I'm manifesting a career
as a vet.

00:09.577 --> 00:12.311
So I'm burning a little piece
of Churro's fur.

00:14.615 --> 00:15.447
Too late.

00:15.483 --> 00:17.149
I already got it
when she was sleeping.

00:18.285 --> 00:20.853
- I'm also man-ifesting.

00:20.888 --> 00:23.822
So I'm burning some of the hair
of the man I have my eye on.

00:23.858 --> 00:25.724
- Oh.
- Did you really cut

00:25.760 --> 00:27.893
some of his hair off?
- Oh, girl, no.

00:27.928 --> 00:29.261
I'm not crazy.

00:29.296 --> 00:30.696
I got it in the garbage
in the alley

00:30.731 --> 00:31.830
behind his barber shop.

00:31.866 --> 00:34.166
- [laughs]

00:34.201 --> 00:36.101
Well, careful, Mayan.

00:36.137 --> 00:38.771
Burning animal fur
is used to curse someone.

00:38.806 --> 00:39.905
How do you think George got

00:39.940 --> 00:41.740
that weird patch of hair
on his ass?

00:44.478 --> 00:47.913
Maybe we should just say
a chant for prosperity instead.

00:47.948 --> 00:50.449
- Ooh, I have one. Okay.

00:50.484 --> 00:53.552
May the spirits help us
secure the bag,

00:53.587 --> 00:56.522
and may our perky asses
never sag.

00:56.557 --> 00:58.657
both: Ah!

00:58.692 --> 01:01.593
[all giggling]

01:01.629 --> 01:03.629
- Ah, ladies, uh,
safety precaution.

01:03.664 --> 01:06.331
Our homeowners policy
doesn't cover<i> brujería.</i>

01:08.669 --> 01:11.503
- Come on, are you<i> brujas</i>
still messing with the spirits?

01:11.539 --> 01:13.272
It's hard to rest in peace
with Rosie's voice

01:13.307 --> 01:15.074
making the ghosts' ears bleed.

01:15.109 --> 01:19.178
-<i> Ay,</i> go shave your ass,
<i>viejito.</i>

01:19.213 --> 01:20.779
- You believe this stuff,
George?

01:20.815 --> 01:23.482
- 'Course I do. I'm Latino.
I believe in ghosts,

01:23.517 --> 01:25.751
Raider Nation, and that Vick's
VapoRub can cure cancer.

01:25.786 --> 01:28.387
You don't?

01:28.422 --> 01:29.922
- Quentin's a nonbeliever.

01:29.957 --> 01:31.723
- I am a spiritual person.

01:31.759 --> 01:33.926
I meditate. I practice yoga.

01:33.961 --> 01:35.327
I just don't think
that there are

01:35.362 --> 01:36.962
actual spirits among us.

01:36.997 --> 01:39.898
I tolerate all of this because
it is what Mayan believes in.

01:39.934 --> 01:41.166
- You should watch
your back, nerd,

01:41.202 --> 01:42.868
because believe
or don't believe,

01:42.903 --> 01:45.737
this house is haunted.

01:48.843 --> 01:50.976
Oh, the other night I saw
a shadow in Chance's room,

01:51.011 --> 01:52.978
and I caught it on video
on my phone.

01:53.013 --> 01:56.482
Look.
- [gasps]

01:56.517 --> 01:58.217
- Funny, that "shadow"
is shaped

01:58.252 --> 02:02.154
just like George's p...
I'm gonna say thumb.

02:02.189 --> 02:04.223
- That's not my thumb.
But just to be clear,

02:04.258 --> 02:05.724
my thumb is much bigger
than that.

02:05.759 --> 02:06.758
- Ohh.

02:06.794 --> 02:09.695
<i>[upbeat saxophone music]</i>

02:09.730 --> 02:16.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:23.210 --> 02:25.377
- Boom!
[cackles]

02:25.412 --> 02:28.113
I win.
Suck on that candy, grandson.

02:28.149 --> 02:30.616
[laughs]

02:36.457 --> 02:38.757
- This game doesn't feel
very kid-friendly.

02:38.792 --> 02:41.493
Why do you keep on winning
and not the kid?

02:42.196 --> 02:45.030
- Well, I get a little help
from my Tía Azu.

02:45.065 --> 02:48.100
She's my Candyland
spirit guide.

02:49.403 --> 02:51.370
She died of diabetes.

02:53.874 --> 02:55.541
- Nah, I'm not buying it.

02:55.576 --> 02:56.742
- You don't believe in spirits?

02:56.777 --> 02:59.044
Your grandpa says that you saw
a ghost the other night

02:59.079 --> 03:00.712
in your bedroom.

03:00.748 --> 03:03.415
- My daddy told me there's
no such thing as ghosts

03:03.450 --> 03:05.317
just like there's no land
made of candy.

03:05.352 --> 03:07.619
If there was, I would be
on a bus right now.

03:09.823 --> 03:11.623
- No, your dad is wrong.

03:11.659 --> 03:13.692
You want me to tell you
about the little girl

03:13.727 --> 03:15.260
with no face
that used to visit me

03:15.296 --> 03:17.129
when I was your age?

03:18.632 --> 03:21.600
- I feel like I should say no

03:21.635 --> 03:23.902
but I'm a kid, and I don't know
boundaries yet,

03:23.938 --> 03:25.370
so go ahead.

03:25.406 --> 03:30.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:30.477 --> 03:32.077
- Dad, I thought we agreed
not to let

03:32.112 --> 03:33.478
the dirty dishes pile up.

03:33.514 --> 03:35.681
- Oh, that wasn't me, Mayan.
That was the ghost.

03:36.951 --> 03:39.451
Oh, and before you ask,
he also brought

03:39.486 --> 03:43.088
the trash back in
after I took it out.

03:43.123 --> 03:45.857
- Okay, just because we may
have a spirit in the house,

03:45.893 --> 03:47.426
doesn't mean you can blame
everything on it.

03:47.461 --> 03:49.027
- If it gets to haunt us,

03:49.063 --> 03:50.462
why can't we blame stuff on it?

03:50.497 --> 03:53.765
Hey, it's called trickle-down
ecto-nomics, Mayan.

03:53.801 --> 03:55.500
Read a book.

03:56.470 --> 03:58.637
- I'm here.
- Oh.

03:58.672 --> 04:01.673
- And like the moon and the
wind and the stars,

04:01.709 --> 04:03.208
I am everywhere.

04:11.685 --> 04:13.352
- Rosie, don't be bringing
your weird dates

04:13.387 --> 04:15.420
into the kitchen.

04:15.456 --> 04:17.756
- This is not my date.
This is Carlos.

04:17.791 --> 04:18.857
He's a<i> curandero</i>

04:18.892 --> 04:22.494
that will help protect us
from attacks by spirits

04:22.529 --> 04:24.896
from the other side.
- Mm.

04:24.932 --> 04:27.799
You have a spirit,
I can clear it.

04:29.370 --> 04:32.838
If you're bothered,
give me a holler.

04:32.873 --> 04:37.342
If you're possessed,
I'm the best.

04:37.378 --> 04:39.378
And I take
all major credit cards,

04:39.413 --> 04:41.713
cash, and now bitcoin.

04:43.384 --> 04:44.416
- Well, I don't have
any of those,

04:44.451 --> 04:47.753
but how about a joint?

04:47.788 --> 04:50.722
You strike me
as that kind of guy.

04:50.758 --> 04:54.026
- No, I never touch the stuff.

04:54.061 --> 04:58.230
Wait, I sense an evil,
dark presence among us.

04:58.866 --> 05:01.667
- Yeah, she's standing
right next to you.

05:01.702 --> 05:03.869
That blazer is hiding
her bat wings.

05:03.904 --> 05:06.038
[imitates wings flapping]

05:06.073 --> 05:08.040
-<i> Ay,</i> keep talking

05:08.075 --> 05:11.243
and you'll be able to braid
that ass hair by tomorrow.

05:13.147 --> 05:17.015
- It is very strong
in this kitchen.

05:17.051 --> 05:18.684
- Well, then I'm going
in the living room.

05:18.719 --> 05:20.152
Girl, bye.

05:20.187 --> 05:22.454
- It's on the move.
- Oh.

05:24.491 --> 05:26.758
- It's coming--
coming from his direction.

05:26.794 --> 05:30.862
- All right, come on, man.
Take it easy.

05:30.898 --> 05:32.264
<i>Ay,</i> I don't like you
like that, all right?

05:34.702 --> 05:37.903
- Yes. Yes,
someone from beyond has,

05:37.938 --> 05:40.706
in the words
of our ancient ancestors,

05:40.741 --> 05:43.775
got major beef with you, homes.

05:45.946 --> 05:49.147
- Wait, there's someone
angry enough with you

05:49.183 --> 05:52.217
to spend their entire afterlife
haunting you?

05:52.252 --> 05:53.985
[chuckles]
Well, that could only be

05:54.021 --> 05:56.788
anyone you've ever met.

05:56.824 --> 05:57.723
- Wait a minute,
that's not true.

05:57.758 --> 05:59.124
I got along with everyone.

05:59.159 --> 06:00.625
- Well, not everyone.

06:00.661 --> 06:02.060
Your Tío Hugo never forgave you

06:02.096 --> 06:06.198
for saying his beard looked
like chin mold.

06:06.233 --> 06:08.200
- Yes, and if old "Fungus Face"
would have got

06:08.235 --> 06:10.435
that checked out earlier,

06:10.471 --> 06:12.471
maybe he'd still be with us.

06:13.640 --> 06:15.607
- No, it-it's none
of those people.

06:15.642 --> 06:18.610
I sense an older woman

06:18.645 --> 06:22.414
whose first name begins
with the letter "D."

06:22.449 --> 06:24.850
- [gasps]
- Oh, Dolores.

06:24.885 --> 06:26.451
- Oh, that's George's
grandmother.

06:26.487 --> 06:28.487
She raised him in this house.
- Mm-hmm.

06:28.522 --> 06:29.554
- That--no, come on.
That could--

06:29.590 --> 06:31.990
that could be anybody
fr-from...

06:32.025 --> 06:34.326
from Doris Day to Daisy Duck.
I mean, come on.

06:35.629 --> 06:37.262
Definitely not
my Grandma Dolores.

06:37.297 --> 06:39.898
Ow!

06:39.933 --> 06:41.466
What is that?

06:41.502 --> 06:43.101
What is--aw!
- [gasps]

06:44.872 --> 06:46.438
A<i> chancla!</i>

06:51.011 --> 06:55.213
Just like the ones
Dolores used to hit you with.

06:55.249 --> 06:58.116
Thrown from the other side.

06:58.152 --> 07:00.085
- Yes, it's definitely her.

07:00.120 --> 07:01.520
- [sighs]
- Do you two have

07:01.555 --> 07:03.688
any unresolved issues?

07:03.724 --> 07:07.125
- Well, me and that<i> bruja</i>
always had issues,

07:07.161 --> 07:12.063
but they were resolved nicely
when she died.

07:12.099 --> 07:14.766
- Well, that's not
what she's saying.

07:14.802 --> 07:16.301
As a matter of fact,
she's not saying anything.

07:16.336 --> 07:19.070
She's just holding up
a middle finger.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.107
- Well, I guess
if there could be anything,

07:22.142 --> 07:24.009
it could be the fact
that I canceled her funeral

07:24.044 --> 07:26.311
and then kept the money
and then buried her ashes

07:26.346 --> 07:29.047
in the backyard.
- Oh, my God.

07:29.082 --> 07:31.516
- Well, that'll do it.

07:32.719 --> 07:35.887
- You put Grandma
in the pet cemetery?

07:35.923 --> 07:37.556
Oh, God, she's been spending
eternity

07:37.591 --> 07:40.325
next to my six dead hamsters.

07:40.360 --> 07:41.793
- I see 12.

07:43.730 --> 07:45.997
- We might have replaced
a few of them.

07:46.033 --> 07:48.533
I don't know.

07:48.569 --> 07:49.868
- I can't believe
that you didn't give

07:49.903 --> 07:51.570
your grandma a proper burial.

07:51.605 --> 07:53.538
She raised you
after your mother ran off.

07:53.574 --> 07:54.806
- Yeah,
I know she wasn't perfect,

07:54.842 --> 07:57.342
but at least she didn't let
you grow up on the streets.

07:57.377 --> 07:59.911
- I wish she had.

07:59.947 --> 08:02.414
Homeless people don't have
shoes to hit you with.

08:04.551 --> 08:05.784
- You gotta make this right.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.819
- Yeah. This is disrespectful
even for you.

08:07.855 --> 08:09.588
- And that's disrespectful
to me,

08:09.623 --> 08:10.522
because both of you know

08:10.557 --> 08:13.825
I've been way more
disrespectful than this.

08:16.396 --> 08:18.663
All right, fine.
I'll take care of it.

08:18.699 --> 08:23.101
- Good. Honor Dolores' wishes
or else...

08:23.136 --> 08:24.736
- Or else what?

08:24.771 --> 08:27.439
- Have you ever seen
"Paranormal Activity"?

08:28.942 --> 08:31.576
Spoiler alert,
the family doesn't make it.

08:31.612 --> 08:34.613
-<i> Ay.</i>
<i>- Ay.</i>

08:38.719 --> 08:39.718
- Are you guys asleep?

08:39.753 --> 08:41.686
- Huh?
- [yells]

08:41.722 --> 08:44.723
- You're up.

08:44.758 --> 08:46.391
- I can't sleep.

08:46.426 --> 08:49.561
I'm scared of a ghost
with no face haunting me.

08:49.596 --> 08:51.296
- [sighs] I already told you,
<i>gordo,</i>

08:51.331 --> 08:53.031
there's no such thing
as ghosts.

08:53.066 --> 08:54.799
So you got nothing
to be scared of.

08:54.835 --> 08:56.334
- But Nana said you're wrong.

08:56.370 --> 08:57.836
She also said
you should marry Mom,

08:57.871 --> 09:00.839
but that seemed
like a side trip.

09:00.874 --> 09:03.475
- Yeah. Of course she did.

09:03.510 --> 09:05.310
All right, you can sleep
in bed with us tonight.

09:05.345 --> 09:06.578
Just please make sure
to hit...

09:06.613 --> 09:09.314
[whimpers]

09:09.349 --> 09:11.216
- Did you just see the ghost?

09:11.251 --> 09:13.618
- No. Just some stars.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.721
[groans]

09:16.757 --> 09:19.457
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:19.493 --> 09:21.993
- Hey.
- Well, you look nice.

09:22.029 --> 09:23.228
- Oh, I just finished

09:23.263 --> 09:24.496
my grandmother's, uh,
funeral service

09:24.531 --> 09:25.830
like you asked.

09:25.866 --> 09:27.098
- Really?

09:27.134 --> 09:28.600
But why didn't you include me

09:28.635 --> 09:31.603
or the rest of the family?
- Well, Mayan, you know,

09:31.638 --> 09:34.506
my grandma was
a very private person.

09:34.541 --> 09:36.975
But it was beautiful.
I mean, I...

09:37.010 --> 09:38.577
buried her ashes in the ocean,

09:38.612 --> 09:43.381
and I sang her favorite
Vicente Fernández song.

09:44.952 --> 09:47.586
I felt her spirit move on.

09:47.621 --> 09:48.820
- Hey, George,

09:48.855 --> 09:49.955
you left your beer helmet

09:49.990 --> 09:53.458
and the Blunts and Booze
festival.

09:53.493 --> 09:55.327
- No, I think you mean
I left my beer helmet

09:55.362 --> 09:58.229
at my grandmother's funeral
at the ocean.

09:59.967 --> 10:03.068
- No.

10:03.103 --> 10:07.372
You definitely left it
at the festival.

10:07.407 --> 10:08.440
- Get out.

10:13.847 --> 10:15.814
- I can't believe you lied

10:15.849 --> 10:18.116
about burying Grandma Dolores.

10:18.151 --> 10:19.951
She deserves so much better
than this.

10:19.987 --> 10:22.621
- No, she doesn't, Mayan.

10:22.656 --> 10:25.357
She was an abusive woman
who made my life hell.

10:25.392 --> 10:27.392
And she was not a good person.

10:27.427 --> 10:29.961
- But she was still a person.

10:29.997 --> 10:31.663
I mean, no wonder
her spirit can't rest.

10:31.698 --> 10:33.365
Churro pees on her grave.

10:33.400 --> 10:38.169
- Well, Churro's
not the only one.

10:38.205 --> 10:40.105
- I thought you were
in a better place,

10:40.140 --> 10:42.107
trying to change your life
and to show me

10:42.142 --> 10:43.441
that you could do what's right.

10:43.477 --> 10:45.143
- Yes, for you but not her,
okay?

10:45.178 --> 10:47.612
She's dead
and so is any obligation

10:47.648 --> 10:49.147
to do right by her.

10:49.182 --> 10:51.082
- Her ghost doesn't think so.

10:51.118 --> 10:52.617
And I'm not living
in a haunted house.

10:52.653 --> 10:55.654
So until you find grandma
a proper resting place,

10:55.689 --> 10:58.823
you and your cursed hairy ass
are sleeping in your truck.

10:58.859 --> 11:03.995
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:04.031 --> 11:04.896
- Chance woke me up
at 1:00 a.m.

11:04.931 --> 11:06.431
asking if he could sleep
in bed with us.

11:06.466 --> 11:08.900
He told me you made up
more ghost stories,

11:08.935 --> 11:10.035
and now he's scared again.

11:10.070 --> 11:12.103
- I didn't make up any stories.

11:12.139 --> 11:15.040
Ghosts and spirits
live among us.

11:15.075 --> 11:17.442
Tell him.
[chuckles]

11:19.246 --> 11:21.880
- Ghosts don't exist.

11:21.915 --> 11:23.281
- If they don't exist,

11:23.316 --> 11:25.350
then explain the chancla
that hit George.

11:25.385 --> 11:27.519
- It-it was--
it was Mayan's chancla.

11:27.554 --> 11:29.521
And I put it up on that shelf
to keep it away from Churro.

11:29.556 --> 11:30.722
- Then why did the shelf fall?

11:30.757 --> 11:32.791
- Well, that's easy.
George hung it.

11:36.296 --> 11:39.264
- Spirituality
is part of my culture.

11:39.299 --> 11:41.132
It's been passed down
for generations.

11:41.168 --> 11:42.634
Just like your culture
passed down

11:42.669 --> 11:47.172
baseball, apple pie,
and racism.

11:52.412 --> 11:55.380
Quentin, it's how we heal
each other

11:55.415 --> 11:57.716
and-and honor our ancestors.

11:57.751 --> 12:02.554
- I am fine with you and Mayan
believing whatever you want.

12:02.589 --> 12:05.590
I come alive
on<i> Día de Los Muertos.</i>

12:12.599 --> 12:15.400
I just don't want it forced
on my son.

12:16.803 --> 12:20.371
- So you're okay
with me taking care of him,

12:20.407 --> 12:24.109
cooking for him,
but spirituality is off-limits?

12:25.712 --> 12:26.778
- Yes. [laughs]

12:26.813 --> 12:31.282
Exactly. That's--wow.
Thank you for understanding.

12:31.318 --> 12:33.418
- Does this look like a face
of understanding?

12:35.155 --> 12:37.188
- I don't know.
All I see is beauty.

12:40.694 --> 12:43.261
Look, I just--I just--
I want to limit

12:43.296 --> 12:45.430
his exposure
to things that are scary

12:45.465 --> 12:48.099
and have no basis in reality.

12:48.135 --> 12:50.001
All right? We'll talk later.

12:50.036 --> 12:53.671
I am late for a battle
with a level 26 Demogorgon.

12:55.342 --> 13:01.079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:01.114 --> 13:04.449
- [groaning]

13:04.484 --> 13:05.950
I shouldn't be in here.

13:05.986 --> 13:08.486
This is all your fault.

13:08.522 --> 13:10.655
What do you want from me,
old woman?

13:10.690 --> 13:12.490
Oh, I'm sorry.

13:12.526 --> 13:14.659
Let me speak to you
in your native tongue.

13:14.694 --> 13:16.361
[hisses]

13:17.531 --> 13:18.830
Ow!

13:19.833 --> 13:21.766
- You are always wrong,
<i>baboso.</i>

13:21.802 --> 13:23.301
- [gasps]

13:28.241 --> 13:31.142
Actually,
it's more like this...

13:31.178 --> 13:33.812
[jibbers]
- Oh, man. Come on.

13:37.784 --> 13:41.653
- No, I'm Beetlejuice.

13:41.688 --> 13:43.721
What are you thinking?

13:43.757 --> 13:45.390
- I'm thinking
that those mushrooms

13:45.425 --> 13:47.659
Oscar put in my burger
were not portabello.

13:50.063 --> 13:51.029
What are you doing back here?

13:51.064 --> 13:53.765
The dead hamsters
kicked you out, didn't they?

13:55.368 --> 13:58.102
- Please, I ate the hamsters.

13:58.905 --> 14:01.206
Listen, another anniversary
of my death has come,

14:01.241 --> 14:04.576
and you still haven't
laid me to rest properly.

14:04.611 --> 14:07.178
So I'm gonna have to make you.

14:07.214 --> 14:09.080
- You can't make me do
anything anymore.

14:09.115 --> 14:10.582
- Oh, you think?

14:10.617 --> 14:12.984
[jibbers]
- Oh! Come on, stop.

14:15.388 --> 14:17.722
- Ah, just the same
little bitch you were

14:17.757 --> 14:19.691
when you were six.

14:24.998 --> 14:27.165
- And you're still that same
little 90-pound demon

14:27.200 --> 14:29.000
you always were.

14:29.035 --> 14:32.237
- Hey, Mayan forgave you
for being a horrible father.

14:32.272 --> 14:34.005
Why can't you forgive me?

14:34.040 --> 14:36.708
That makes you a hippo-critter.

14:37.277 --> 14:40.945
- You mean a hypocrite?
- I said what I said.

14:40.981 --> 14:43.047
- Well, I was a lot nicer
to Mayan

14:43.083 --> 14:44.883
than you were to me. Okay?

14:44.918 --> 14:46.951
You used to lock me
in that damn closet.

14:46.987 --> 14:49.954
- You think you had it bad?

14:49.990 --> 14:52.624
I was the eldest of nine,
which made me

14:52.659 --> 14:55.260
the cook, the maid, the nanny.

14:55.295 --> 14:57.262
And if I didn't keep
my mouth shut,

14:57.297 --> 15:00.465
it made me Mommy's
punching bag.

15:00.500 --> 15:03.501
It got so bad
that I didn't speak for months

15:03.536 --> 15:05.770
just trying to avoid a beating.

15:05.805 --> 15:08.940
So do me a favor,
don't harass me with your--

15:08.975 --> 15:11.142
with your little tales
of horror.

15:11.177 --> 15:14.312
Mine would make you beg
for the closet.

15:17.684 --> 15:19.651
- I didn't know.

15:19.686 --> 15:21.185
- Well, now you do.

15:22.822 --> 15:25.823
I was carrying around
a lot of anger.

15:25.859 --> 15:28.493
And I guess
I took it out on you.

15:28.528 --> 15:31.896
- I think Mayan would call this
generational trauma.

15:31.932 --> 15:34.899
- I call it Gen Z<i> caca.</i>
- [laughs]

15:35.902 --> 15:39.237
- Hey, it wasn't all bad.

15:39.272 --> 15:41.973
Hey, you remember
when we would go to the casino?

15:42.008 --> 15:43.308
Yeah?
- Yeah.

15:43.343 --> 15:45.176
- And, uh, I taught you
how to steal change

15:45.211 --> 15:47.445
from the<i> viejitas.</i>
- Right.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.013
You taught me to target
the old ladies

15:49.049 --> 15:51.549
with the hearing aids
and the thick glasses.

15:51.584 --> 15:55.186
- So forgive me and spread
my ashes, already.

15:55.221 --> 15:56.821
Because if you don't,
I'm gonna have to think

15:56.856 --> 15:59.057
of new ways to haunt you.

15:59.092 --> 16:01.259
Like, uh,
every time you drink a Modelo,

16:01.294 --> 16:06.164
it'll taste like, um,
White Claw.

16:06.199 --> 16:08.399
- No!

16:10.337 --> 16:13.271
<i>[gentle music]</i>

16:13.306 --> 16:19.243
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:20.747 --> 16:23.948
<i>[sitar music]</i>

16:23.984 --> 16:26.351
- Daddy, you're meditating
without me.

16:26.386 --> 16:29.854
You know my third chakra
has been blocked.

16:29.889 --> 16:34.058
- Ooh, tell me more
about these chakras.

16:34.094 --> 16:35.960
- Daddy says
there's seven different colors,

16:35.996 --> 16:37.195
and they're all over your body.

16:37.230 --> 16:39.731
There's even one on my butt.

16:40.400 --> 16:42.867
- He's still learning.
They're your energy points.

16:42.902 --> 16:44.168
And in the Vedic tradition,

16:44.204 --> 16:45.770
it is very important
to keep them unblocked.

16:45.805 --> 16:47.872
- Oh, interesting.

16:47.907 --> 16:51.075
So a practice from brown people
in another continent is okay

16:51.111 --> 16:53.277
but not from the brown people
in your own home?

16:55.115 --> 16:57.749
- You know what, Rosie?
- What?

16:57.784 --> 17:00.051
- You just made
an excellent point.

17:00.086 --> 17:02.787
- Oh. I was about to take
my earrings off.

17:04.424 --> 17:06.724
I-I am sorry
that I disrespected

17:06.760 --> 17:09.093
your beliefs just because
they were different than mine.

17:09.129 --> 17:11.496
- And I'm sorry
that I scared Chance.

17:12.866 --> 17:15.633
The ghost actually had a face.
[chuckles]

17:15.668 --> 17:17.869
Tell him you had a face.

17:17.904 --> 17:22.240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:22.275 --> 17:24.409
- Dad, what did you do
to the backyard?

17:24.444 --> 17:26.878
- I was trying to find
my grandma's ashes.

17:26.913 --> 17:28.746
Can't remember where I put her.

17:28.782 --> 17:29.947
- What changed your mind?

17:29.983 --> 17:33.217
- I took a real hard look
at myself, Mayan,

17:33.253 --> 17:36.120
real deep dive into the deepest
parts of my soul.

17:36.156 --> 17:38.823
- So you saw her ghost?
- Oh, yeah.

17:38.858 --> 17:40.358
Maybe she deserves a funeral.

17:40.393 --> 17:42.794
She wants me to forgive her,
but...

17:42.829 --> 17:44.128
I just don't know
if I can do that.

17:44.164 --> 17:46.631
- Well, have you ever tried?

17:46.666 --> 17:49.434
I mean, it was really hard
to forgive you.

17:49.469 --> 17:50.301
- And I'm really glad
that you did, Mayan.

17:50.336 --> 17:53.838
I needed it.
- I didn't do it for you.

17:53.873 --> 17:56.407
I did it for me,
to let go of the past.

17:58.311 --> 17:59.444
[Churro barking]

17:59.479 --> 18:00.645
What's up, girl?

18:00.680 --> 18:03.381
- Churro found
my grandmother's ashes.

18:03.416 --> 18:08.986
- Wait, is this the liquor bag
you told me was a puppet?

18:09.022 --> 18:11.589
- Count Tipsy von Whiskey.

18:11.624 --> 18:13.558
I want to drink your booze.

18:18.965 --> 18:22.567
- Okay. What do you see
in my tea leaves?

18:22.602 --> 18:24.702
- [gasps]

18:24.737 --> 18:31.409
In your future I see
something large, sparkly,

18:31.444 --> 18:33.911
and princess cut.

18:36.049 --> 18:37.582
- Dad, we got a major problem.

18:37.617 --> 18:39.550
- Perfect timing, son.
What's wrong?

18:39.586 --> 18:40.651
- The ghost put
a bunch of holes

18:40.687 --> 18:43.321
in our backyard,
and I'm scared.

18:43.356 --> 18:45.289
Luckily I found
these brass knuckles

18:45.325 --> 18:47.658
in one of them
to protect myself.

18:47.694 --> 18:49.560
- Okay, let's--
[chuckles].

18:49.596 --> 18:52.363
Just gonna--gonna take those.

18:52.398 --> 18:55.733
There's, uh--there's nothing
to be scared of.

18:55.768 --> 18:58.736
Right, Rosie?
- That's right.

18:58.771 --> 19:00.571
A ghost didn't do that
to your backyard.

19:00.607 --> 19:02.540
A drunk troll did.
- [chuckles]

19:02.575 --> 19:05.409
- Come,<i> gordo,</i> sit over here.

19:05.445 --> 19:08.045
No ghost is going to hurt you.

19:08.081 --> 19:10.114
Any spirits in this house

19:10.150 --> 19:13.184
are just family
watching over us.

19:13.219 --> 19:14.852
- Does that mean after we die

19:14.888 --> 19:16.320
our family will all be
together again?

19:16.356 --> 19:18.556
- Yep. That's exactly
what that means.

19:18.591 --> 19:20.358
- So now I have forever
to figure out

19:20.393 --> 19:22.760
how to beat you in Candyland.

19:22.795 --> 19:25.763
- Yup. But that's never
gonna happen, chump.

19:25.798 --> 19:29.667
[chuckles]
- Nana, who hurt you?

19:32.505 --> 19:34.772
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:34.807 --> 19:36.574
- Why did we bring
Grandma's ashes

19:36.609 --> 19:38.676
to a Walter Mercado penny slot?

19:38.711 --> 19:41.679
<i>- All signs point to big win.</i>

19:41.714 --> 19:43.881
- This is
where she was the happiest.

19:43.917 --> 19:46.784
Actually, it's where we were
the happiest together.

19:46.819 --> 19:48.653
Yeah, you know, I thought
about what you said, Mayan.

19:48.688 --> 19:50.354
And this is the right thing
to do.

19:50.390 --> 19:51.389
- Would you like
to say anything

19:51.424 --> 19:52.356
before you spread her ashes?

19:52.392 --> 19:54.258
You know, quickly,
before anyone catches us.

19:54.294 --> 19:57.128
- Yeah, uh...

19:57.163 --> 19:58.763
Okay,<i> vieja,</i>

19:58.798 --> 20:00.798
I'm not doing this for you.

20:00.833 --> 20:05.469
I'm doing it for me,
to let go of the past.

20:05.505 --> 20:08.806
I don't deserve much,
but I deserve to be free.

20:08.841 --> 20:13.211
Rest in peace
<i>con mucho, mucho amor.</i>

20:13.246 --> 20:17.582
<i>- Mucho, mucho amor.</i>

20:17.617 --> 20:21.085
<i>Play now for your fortune.</i>

20:23.623 --> 20:24.589
- Oh, we've been caught.

20:24.624 --> 20:25.756
Dump the old lady and run.

20:25.792 --> 20:27.425
<i>- Muchi, mucho dinero.</i>

20:27.460 --> 20:29.060
- Ahh!
- Ugh.

20:29.095 --> 20:30.695
I got my grandma in my eye!

20:33.199 --> 20:37.301
- Ooh, that big-headed Georgie
finally did something right.

20:37.337 --> 20:40.004
[gasps]
Okay, Walter...

20:41.374 --> 20:44.008
[slot machine trills]

20:44.043 --> 20:45.009
[gasps] Oh!

20:45.044 --> 20:46.510
<i>- Jackpot!</i>

20:46.546 --> 20:49.046
<i>$100,000!</i>
- Oh, my God!

20:49.082 --> 20:50.448
<i>You're rich!</i>

20:50.483 --> 20:53.017
- I won. I won.
I won the jackpot.

20:53.052 --> 20:55.519
This is the best day
of my afterlife.

20:55.555 --> 21:02.026
[bellowing]

21:02.061 --> 21:03.427
- Damn.

21:03.463 --> 21:05.029
Being a<i> curandero</i>
doesn't pay

21:05.064 --> 21:07.131
like what it used to.

21:07.166 --> 21:11.869
Hmm, I wonder if this casino
takes bitcoin.

21:11.904 --> 21:14.805
<i>- Whoa! Oh, no. No, no.</i>
<i>No, no.</i>

21:14.841 --> 21:16.774
<i>Let me out of here.</i>

21:16.809 --> 21:19.910
<i>Where's a chancla</i>
<i>when you need one?</i>
